    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <description>Insert compiler instructions to ignore the generated files when the FxCop analyzer runs.</description>
    <releaseNotes>Restored the functionality of 1.3.0 where the tool would recurse into the intermediate subdirectories.</releaseNotes>
    <summary>
      The code analyzers expects all modules that they inspect to be properly documented.  This is a serious problem for
      generated code, especially the kind generated from Windows 8 and Windows 10 development.  The intermediate files
      generate copious amounts of warnings for code the programmer can't change.  Oddly, Microsoft doesn't automatically place
      pragmas in generated code which would inhibit the these useless warnings.  This package adds task that will go through
      the intermediate files at all levels and add the pragmas that instruct the compiler to ignore documentation warnings.
    </summary>
